1476.name: Chas Meyer
1476.notes:
I will only sign personal keys (no group or organization keys) and the
following will be how I assign check level:

0 (no claim) -	I won't sign at this level

1 (believe key to belong to presenter, but not verified) - I will sign at
this level upon the presentation of a single form of non-Texas-DPS
government issued photo ID. If I deem you to have a common name, we will
need to verify your access to the email addresses listed on your key.

2 (casual verification) - I will sign at this level upon presentation of a
valid Texas DPS issued ID or the presentation of both a non-Texas-DPS
government issued photo ID along with either a valid US Military ID or a
valid US passport. Additionally, we will need to test your access to the
email addresses listed in your key IDs.

3 (extensive verification) - I will sign at this level upon presentation
of a valid Texas DPS issued ID along with a valid US passport. The email
test described in (2) will also need to be performed. Additionally, I will
perform a casual google search on your identity to ensure that there are
no red flags indicating you might not be who you claim to be.

Note that the evaluation of the legitimacy of all IDs for this purpose is
solely at my discretion.

Additionally, this list is in no way to be considered binding. I, at all
times, reserve the right to sign or not sign a key at whatever check level
I choose for any reason whatsoever.

I hope you all choose to be at least as rigorous (if not more) as I am in
signing and assigning check levels to others' public keys. Lets remember
that the web of trust only works when we all evaluate each other to the
best of our abilities.
